import { useState } from 'react'
import ReactCardFlip from 'react-card-flip'
import { Box, Card, Container, Grid, makeStyles, Grow, Paper } from '@material-ui/core'
import Image from 'material-ui-image'
import Typography from '@material-ui/core/Typography'
import useStyles from './styles'
import abstractImage from '../../images/Abstract-Envelope.svg'
import vectorAvacado from '../../images/simpleAvacado.png'

const Home = () => {
    const classes = useStyles()
    const [isFlipped, setIsFlipped] = useState(false)

    return (
        <Grid container justify='center' direction='column' >
            <Grid item md={6}>
                <Paper className={classes.imageDisplay} borderRadius='10px'>
                    <Image src={abstractImage} cover/>
                </Paper>
            </Grid>
        </Grid>
    )
}

export default Home
